  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nCurrent naming is verbose.\r\n`import {...} from \"@chainsafe/lodestar-config\"`\r\n`import {...} from \"@chainsafe/lodestar-types\"`\r\n`import {...} from \"@chainsafe/lodestar-beacon-state-transition\"`\r\n`import {...} from \"@chainsafe/lodestar-cli\"`\r\netc.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n`import {...} from \"@lodestar/config\"`\r\n`import {...} from \"@lodestar/types\"`\r\n`import {...} from \"@lodestar/beacon-state-transition\"`\r\n`import {...} from \"@lodestar/cli\"`\r\netc.\r\n\r\nI think its clear (from community knowledge, copyright notices, github organization, etc) that ChainSafe owns and manages lodestar. We likely don't need the additional explicit reminder in the package name, itself.\r\n\r\nA more concise package name is generally a good thing for memorability and usability.\r\nWe may also shorten each monorepo directory name (eg: `./packages/lodestar-validator` -> `./packages/validator`)\r\nHaving simpler naming may make it more convenient to add more monorepo packages w/o incurring the pain of searching thru a long list of `lodestar-*` packages/directories.\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\nleave as-is",
